      "writtenOn": "2020-09-08T13:14:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The enum values don\u0027t need to be perfectly packed; AFAICS we could just base everything on sentinel enums:\n\nenum Kind {\n  kStartSentinel \u003d LastIRNodeType::Kind::kEndSentinel,\n  kFoo,\n  kBar,\n  kEndSentinel,\n\n  kFirst \u003d kStartSentinel + 1,\n  kLast \u003d kEndSentinel - 1\n};\n\nNow someone adding a new Kind does not need to change any of the other lines.",
